race.comment: LADIES PRO (8) was a dominant winner on debut over 1000m, with her late strength the highlight of her 1.7L win. The sharp rise in trip is a query, though her breeding and late splits suggest it's not a problem. Can remain unbeaten in what looks a suitable race. HEWILLDOUS (4) stuck on well at Geraldton last time out and turned in a good figure in the process. Third-up now and well placed from the barrier. Can put his best foot forward. MANJERI (2) steps out in trip today but his last two wins have been impressive. Can bring up the hat-trick. ODIN OMEN (9) is a first-up winner in the past and makes some appeal down in the weights.
